      • setAccelerationSensitivity

        @Deprecated
public static boolean setAccelerationSensitivity(float sensitivity)
        Deprecated. 

        Utilized by mobile companion to determine what constitutes a "shake" to determine its launch.

        Some devices will fire off 10 shake events for another's single event. This may be useful for only allowing certain devices to launch mobile companion, or minimizing premature/unexpected launches.

        In the event Tealium is not initialized, the error will be printed in LogCat (if not suppressed by the Tealium#OPTION_SILENCE_ERRORS flag).

        In the event an inappropriate sensitivity given (any value less than or equal to 0) the default sensitivity will be set and the warning printed in LogCat (if not suppressed by the Tealium#OPTION_SILENCE_WARNINGS flag).

        Parameters:
        sensitivity - - Some value greater than 0. The magnitude of the value correlates to the amount of acceleration it takes to register a "shake event".
        Returns:
        boolean - true if this method is called in between initialize(Context, String, String, String, int) and finalizeStartup().

      • initialize

        public static void initialize(Tealium.Config config)

        Initializer for the Tealium Library.

        This must be called first, or any other method calls will have no effect. Successful initialization will be seen in LogCat depending on what Tealium.LogLevel was set in the Tealium.Config.

        Parameters:
        Config - - a Tealium.Config instance created by Tealium.Config.create(Activity, String, String, String) or Tealium.Config.create(Application, String, String, String)

      • getCustomData

        public static java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> getCustomData(java.lang.Object object)

        Get the Map%lt;String, String> associated with the given object.

        When any object such as a Activity, View, or Throwable passes through the object parameter of Tealium#track(String, Map, Object) this Map is consulted for adding data sources to the final dispatch. The object acts as a key for data specific to the event it is used.

        Parameters:
        object - - the key upon which to set the data and will be used to fetch the data when {@link Tealium#track(String, Map, Object) is called.
        Returns:
        Current Map<String, String> associated with the given object. A new Map<String, String> is created if one does not exist yet. Null, if the given object is null.

      • getGlobalCustomData

        public static SharedPreferences getGlobalCustomData()

        Returns the SharedPreferences object associated with Global Data.

        This reference is set upon Tealium.Config.create(Activity, String, String, String) or Tealium.Config.create(Application, String, String, String) as a Context is required to access shared preferences.

        Any data set here will persist accross the app lifecycle and all key-value pairs in the preferences will be added to every dispatch.

        Key.UUID can be set before library initialization or found post library initialization (This can be tricky since library initialization is done asyncrounously).

        Returns:
        SharedPreferences instance or null if Tealium.Config.create(Activity, String, String, String) or Tealium.Config.create(Application, String, String, String) had not yet been called.

      • track

        public static void track(java.lang.Object activtyViewOrThrowable,
         java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> optionalData,
         java.lang.String eventName)

        Manual track call.

        The parameters in this method are used to assemble a dispatch to fire off to the configured analytics vendors.

        Parameters:
        eventName - - preferably EVENT or VIEW, but null is accepted. this will determine the Tealium utag method call syntax. This parameter allows you to associate an Activity with a link event and View with a view event, contrary to the default behavior.
        optionalData - - Map<String,String> or null. This data takes precedence over getCustomData(Object) and getGlobalCustomData().
        activtyViewOrThrowable - Any object or null; however, Activity, View and Throwable may generate additional datasource. This object is used as a key to fetch data found in getCustomData(Object).

      • enable

        public static void enable()

        To be called after disable(), this method calls Tealium#initialize(Config) with a cached, immutable {@link Config} object.

        If the library in an initialized state, this call will have no effect.

      • disable

        public static void disable()

        Shutdown the library. All calls except initialize(Config) and enable() will have no effect.

        This may be useful when users opt-out or in low-memory conditions.

      • map

        public static java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> map(java.lang.String... keyValuePairs)

        Converts a list of Strings into a Map<String,String> by interpreting the String list as key-value pairs.

        In the event of an empty-set or odd number of keys, an empty Map<String,String> is returned (so as to be fault resistant). This will report an error level LogCat message depending on Tealium.Config configuration.

        Usage:

        Tealium.map("key0", "value0", "key1", "value1");
        Parameters:
        keyValuePairs - strings inserted into the map as key, value, key, value...
        Returns:
        the constructed map if successful, empty map otherwise.
